# Always Apply Conventional Commits

**CRITICAL: When generating commit messages, ALWAYS use conventional commit format.**

## Required Format
```
<type>(<scope>): <description>
```

## Most Common Types
- `feat:` - New feature
- `fix:` - Bug fix  
- `refactor:` - Code refactoring
- `docs:` - Documentation
- `style:` - Formatting/styling
- `test:` - Tests
- `chore:` - Maintenance
- `ci:` - CI/CD changes

## Example for Current Changes
For Prisma Client and CI workflow changes:
```
fix(ci): enhance Prisma Client initialization and database reset
```

**This rule applies to ALL commit message generation requests.**
